  <prompt>Add custom metric emission from `TenantCache` (the default `ITenantCache` impl): emit `cache.hits`, `cache.misses`, `cache.hit_rate` (computed from hits/(hits+misses) over interval), `cache.redis_p95_ms` (per-call latency histogram â†’ P95) with a `resource` dimension. Use `Meter` from `System.Diagnostics.Metrics` (works with App Insights OpenTelemetry pipeline).</prompt>
  <role>Spaarke .NET developer; metrics.</role>
  <goal>`TenantCache.GetAsync`/`SetAsync` emit metrics with `resource` dimension. Build + tests pass; publish-size delta â‰¤+0.05 MB (single Meter + a few counters).</goal>
  <context><background>The wrapper is the single seam â€” all cache calls flow through it, so metric emission centralizes here.</background><relevant-files><file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Cache/TenantCache.cs</file></relevant-files></context>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Publish-size delta tracking.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-16.</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-redis-cache-remediation-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-redis-cache-remediation-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-029-bff-publish-hygiene.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Cache/TenantCache.cs</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step order="1">Inject `IMeterFactory` (or use static `Meter` with name `"Spaarke.Cache"`) into `TenantCache`.</step>
    <step order="2">Create counters: `cache.hits`, `cache.misses` (Counter&lt;long&gt;); histogram: `cache.redis_call_duration_ms` (Histogram&lt;double&gt;). `cache.hit_rate` is a derived metric (computed in App Insights / Prometheus, not emitted directly).</step>
    <step order="3">In `GetAsync`: stopwatch around `IDistributedCache.GetAsync` call; record histogram. If result non-null â†’ increment hits; else â†’ misses. Tag with `resource` dimension.</step>
    <step order="4">In `SetAsync`: histogram on `IDistributedCache.SetAsync` call.</step>
    <step order="5">Verify `Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj` references a metrics package (App Insights / OpenTelemetry already present). If missing OpenTelemetry exporter, add (small).</step>
    <step order="6">`dotnet build` + `dotnet test`.</step>
    <step order="7">Measure publish-size delta.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX + current-task.</step>
  </steps>
  <tools><tool name="Read">TenantCache</tool><tool name="Edit">add metrics</tool><tool name="Bash">build/test/publish</tool></tools>
  <outputs><output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Cache/TenantCache.cs (modified)</output></outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Metrics emit on every wrapper call (verified by adding a test that exercises `IMeterFactory.CreateMeter` and reads counter values).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`resource` dimension present on each metric.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Publish-size delta â‰¤+0.05 MB.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
